To come up with this translation, I used my knowledge of English and Mandarin Chinese languages and my understanding of the lyrics' meaning. I noticed that the word "dreary" in English has a similar meaning to the word "沮丧" in Mandarin Chinese. So, I translated the word "dreary" as "沮丧" in the translation. I also considered the context of the lyrics and the emotions

别再忧伤你曾是

The reason for this choice is that the Chinese characters are more concise and expressive, while the English characters are more abstract and more difficult to translate accurately.
